content:
Users can now harness the power of Einstein Copilot to generate a summary of up to five recent customer interactions. With Einstein Copilot, users spend less time on summarizing customer interactions and more time on completing valuable tasks.

To generate the summary, Einstein Copilot taps into the customer interaction information, including transcripts, which are stored in the Engagement Interaction, Messaging Session, or Voice Call records and in the Engagement Topic and Content Document Link related object records.

This change applies to Lightning Experience in clouds where Einstein Copilot is available. 

To use this feature, users need the Industry Service Excellence add-on license and optionally, the Service Cloud Voice and Digital Engagement add-on licenses. To summarize up to five recent customer interactions, submit an utterance in Einstein Copilot from an Account record page.

This feature is a Beta Service.
title: Einstein Copilot Summary Feature for Customer Interactions
